## Runtime scale utility

Define layout values in JavaScript (inline styles), not CSS files. Scale at runtime:

```typescript
const DESIGN_WIDTH = 1920;
const DEVICE_WIDTH = 1280; // detected from PAL or screen
const RATIO = DEVICE_WIDTH / DESIGN_WIDTH;

export function px(designPx: number, roundDown = false): number {
  const scaled = designPx * RATIO;
  return roundDown ? Math.floor(scaled) : Math.ceil(scaled);
}
```

```tsx
<div style={{
  position: 'absolute',
  top: px(60),
  left: px(80),
  width: px(1760, true),
  height: px(400)
}}>
```

- Author all values at 1920x1080. `px()` scales to device resolution at runtime.
- Ceil by default (avoids gaps); floor when arg provided (avoids overflow).
- All values must be whole-number pixels.
